President Donald Trump has declared a state of emergency in South Carolina due to the emergency conditions caused by Hurricane Irma. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources to help alleviate the impacts of the emergency, with 75% of funding coming from the federal government. Willie G. Nunn has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.